Question: Is there any structural error in this JSON? If so, give the answer 'True' and spot them out. If it is free from error, just give the answer 'False'.

Input: 
{
"id":"a",
"Z":"r",
"subs":[
 {
 "id":"b",
 "Y":"q",
 "subs":[
  {
  "id":"c",
  "X":"p",
  "subs":[]
  }
 ]
]

True

There is a structural error in the given JSON. It lacks a closing bracket for the array assigned to the "subs" key of the first object and a closing curly brace for the entire JSON structure.

The corrected JSON should look like this:

```json
{
  "id": "a",
  "Z": "r",
  "subs": [
    {
      "id": "b",
      "Y": "q",
      "subs": [
        {
          "id": "c",
          "X": "p",
          "subs": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

